text: The Frozard Plantation House, near Grand Coteau, Louisiana, was built around 1842 and was expanded in 1901. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1982. It has also been known as the Olivier Plantation. With It is located about south or east of Grand Coteau off Louisiana Highway 93. ==References== Category:Plantations in Louisiana Category:National Register of Historic Places in St. Landry Parish, Louisiana Category:Greek Revival architecture in Louisiana Category:Queen Anne architecture in Louisiana Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1842
